glosses: To grow, to increase in size, to expand.
To grow up, to be brought up.
To grow in age, to age.
To increase in severity or intensity.
To increase in number or amount.

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish بیومك (biyümek) or بویمك (büyümek, “to increase in size, grow, to rise in rank or importance”), from Proto-Turkic *bedü- (“to become bigger, grow”).
Cognates with Crimean Tatar büyümek, Gagauz büümää, Karakhanid بَدُماكْ (beδümek, “to grow up”), Old Uyghur [script needed] (bedü-, “to grow, increase”), Azerbaijani böyümək (“to grow up”), Tuvan бедиир (bediir, “to rise, go up”).
